article.headline: Blue Demons post record C-USA win
article.linkText: DePaul avenges lone C-USA loss vs. Marquette
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- DePaul avenged its only Conference USA loss with
a 77-56 victory over Marquette Sunday.

Jenni Dant scored 29 points for the 12th-ranked Blue Demons
(24-3, 13-1), who matched a league record with their 13th straight
conference win.

DePaul had not lost since a 63-57 defeat to the Golden Eagles in
the conference opener on Jan. 9.

Jenna Rubino and Allie Quigley each added 17 points for DePaul.
The Blue Demons only shot 35 percent in the second half, but were
able to hold of Marquette with 13 3-pointers for the game.

DePaul led 48-28 at halftime and scored 27 points off turnovers
to 11 for the Golden Eagles.

Carolyn Kieger's 15 points led Marquette (17-10, 8-6), which had
won three straight games against DePaul. Lesley Juedes had 12
points and Efueko Osaige added 10.

DePaul clinched the conference title Feb. 20 with a victory over
Memphis. The Blue Demons, whose current ranking matches its best
ever, have won 23 straight games at home. Their other losses this
season were against Purdue and Tennessee.

Sunday's game marked the final regular-season meeting in C-USA.
Both schools are joining the Big East next season.
